<br>
We did the same test 2 or 3 times ideally we would have had a mob that gave a msg everytime taunt was successful though, you are right. <br>
<br>
If I was not in melee range of the mob he was able to taunt succesfully on the first or second taunt everytime.  However if I stopped running and stood there he was not able to taunt the mob off me using 20 taunts. He was able to turn the mob if he attacked for one round with his fists though. So this tells me that one round of melee attacks with your fists adds more hate than 20 taunts. <br>
<br>
Taunt just matches your hate to the top person on the list. It is your attacking right after you taunt that actually turns the mob. I suppose this is why low delay weapons are good for warriors maintaining aggro.<br>
<br>
