<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>How is it that I can toss tash, get summoned, but not hit, because the melee are wailing away and getting hammered?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The ability for a mob to summon and attack are on two seperate timers. If the mob is slowed it would be possible for you to get summoned and either:<br>
<br>
a) have a melee taunt off you or otherwise generate more hate then you, or<br>
b) back away from melee range,<br>
<br>
*before* the mob's attack timer reset.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>How is it that a wizard can toss out, say, giant bane and get annihilated?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Warrior didn't taunt in time, or the taunt failed?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Explain to me the effect of processing weapons.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Everything you do be it slash, kick, snare, tash, slow, nuke, etc... has some amount of hate that is generated along with it. Procs serve to do the same thing (although some procs actually lower hate).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What does something like AE taunt do and how does it differ and for how long?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
AE taunt, unlike regular taunt, will always suceed, and of course it hits all the mobs in some particular radius.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also, does anyone know which mobs are untauntable so I don't waste my time anymore? /grin.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Only through experience. Have someone tash or slow or snare a mob, walk up to it, don't attack, just hit your taunt button. After 10 tries if he doesn't turn on you then I think it's safe to assume that the mob is untauntable. After each try have the other person (the one who has agro) try and back out of melee range just to be sure that taunt failed. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viken>Viken</A> at: 1/15/03 11:52:15 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuggbarg>TuggbarG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/03 12:44:45 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://canflag.ptbcanadian.com/images/animated/provii/cf2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunt button usage</span><hr size=1> Good answers...thanks. <p>Tuggbar Gruntbar<br>
