<br>
But recently with this post I have shifted my style to only taunt when the mob turned. I haven't noticed a significant increase in holding aggro with or without mashing, which leads me to believe taunt shouldnt be used unless the mob turns away from you. I found that by not mashing I could control aggro much more easier. When a mob turned to attack the chanter Id taunt once and he would turn right away back to attack me. <br>
<br>
IMO I think taunt isnt a tool to BUILD / INCREASE aggro, it only serves to regain lost aggro.<br>
<br>
At any rate I think taunt is best used without mashing it every time it pops up. Mashing will not build aggro any more then hitting it occasionally. And you need to be able to hit taunt when the mob turns, so having it mashed all the time really does no good.<br>
<br>
ANyway just my 2cp. Mashing bad. Smart taunting good.<br>
<br>
