<br>
This coupled with other stuff, lead to this statement : The mob CAN be attacking you while OTHERS are on TOP of the HATE LIST.<br>
<br>
The exact mechanism behind that are still kinda unclear.  Could be with a separate list based on the hate list + the modifier like aggro spells, range, sit, snare, etc.<br>
<br>
This stuff is only visible to the tank when someone &quot;overaggro&quot; and the mob summon, pong or switch to another tank.  What is invisible is all the other time that that non-tank was close to over-aggroing but did'nt.  <br>
<br>
Now, we have to assume for now that a successfull taunt will put you on taunt of the actual hate list and not on top of the modified hate list.  This is kinda hard to prove but I'll think about it.<br>
<br>
With this single assumption, the best solution is to taunt all the time when you are tanking *mash*.  It is only worth it to wait for a specific spell when that spell is inc now or else you just lost a chance to gain enough aggro from a previous cast to prevent overaggro instead of taunt after the overaggro has happened.<br>
<br>
Thorbadin<br>
Triton <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ragnok>Ragnok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/17/03 2:14:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: a bit more evidence to throw in..</span><hr size=1> I think most people are just making this issue too complicated. Who cares if there is one list, or there is a modified list. It doesn't matter if your cousins's middle name is george, and It certainly doesn't matter if on every third wednesday a third and fourth list is created just for the hell of it. All that matters is this: If you taunt, and the taunt is successful, and you are as close to the mob as possible, you will get agro. period. Beyond that very very simple fact, you have two choices left:<br>
<br>
1.) You can *mash* the taunt button while you -already- have agro, leaving casters vulnerable until it refreshes.<br>
<br>
a.) If its a melee that keeps getting agro, its his responsibility to stop taking agro, not yours to keep mashing taunt.<br>
b.) If its a caster that got agro, and they are moderately competant, they will see their mistake, and fix it.<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
2.) Use the taunt button as soon as you lose agro. (the definition of the taunt skill.)<br>
<br>
Maybe its because im a gemini, or maybe its because my real name is Rob, but i believe #2 is not only the most efficient way to use this skill, but also the most usefull. *Mashing* taunt removes the little control you have and leaves it up to statistics. Saving taunt for when it needs to be used puts -you- in control of the situation, the relative control that VI gives you anyways. I see no other way.<br>
<br>
Ragnok Gemcrusher<br>
